==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Osculatrix
<hw>Os`cu*la"trix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Osculatrixes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A curve whose contact with a given curve, at a
given point, is of a higher order (or involves the equality of a greater
number of successive differential coefficients of the ordinates of the
curves taken at that point) than that of any other curve of the same
kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oscule</ent>⟦br⟧
